<h2>Accessories Controlled</h2>
Fans, Vents, Misting Systems, Fogging Systems, Heating Systems,and Cooling Systems are all controlled by control systems. The operations can be very simple in nature and provide a great benefit to keeping your greenhouse in perfect shape.

The first stage of implementation can be as simple as an on/off switch to control circulation fans. By semi-automating a control system with a humidistat, a thermostat, or a timing device, the accessories will run only when necessary, lowering operating costs and saving energy. Fully automated systems have the option of being controlled by a semaphore or remote programming system on a PC or even through a cell phone, saving a substantial amount of time. These fully automated systems can be designed to maintain a specific set of criteria for constant plant comfort, taking into account the conditions outside the structure that may affect the plantsâ€™ growing.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-38107" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/greenhouse-control-system.png" alt="" width="680" height="400" />
<h2>Advantages</h2>
<ul>
 	<li><strong>Improve Vegetation Quality</strong>Â â€“ Mimicking a cooler night temperature improves vegetation quality as it more closely simulates the natural environment. Accurate temperature and humidity controls provide uniform growing conditions to increase quality and production.</li>
 	<li><strong>Reduce Fuel Costs</strong>Â â€“ Lowering the greenhouse temperature at night, when 80% of the heating occurs, reduces energy consumption. Centralizing temperature sensors, controlling them with a single unit, prevents heating and cooling systems from running simultaneously.</li>
 	<li><strong>Increase Productivity</strong>Â â€“ Automation allows owners to focus on growing the plants, not adjusting settings.</li>
</ul>
